# Privacy Policy for StickifyCart

Last updated: November 27, 2024

## 1. Introduction
StickifyCart ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of our users ("you", "your"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Shopify application.

## 2. Information We Collect
### 2.1 Store Information
- Basic store information (name, URL, email)
- Theme settings and configurations
- Product and collection information

### 2.2 Customer Information
We do not directly collect or store customer personal information. Any customer interaction data is processed through Shopify's secure infrastructure.

## 3. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:
- Provide and maintain our service
- Customize the app's functionality to your store's needs
- Send important updates about our service
- Respond to support requests

## 4. Data Storage and Security
- All data is stored securely on Shopify's infrastructure
- We implement industry-standard security measures
- Regular security audits and updates are performed

## 5. Third-Party Services
We do not share your information with third parties except as necessary to provide our service through the Shopify platform.

## 6. Your Rights
You have the right to:
- Access your store's data
- Request data deletion
- Opt-out of communications
- Modify app settings

## 7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.

## 8. Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
- Email: evilryu78@proton.me
- GitHub: https://github.com/stickifycart-docs

## 9. Compliance
This app complies with:
- Shopify's API Terms of Service
- GDPR requirements
- CCPA requirements
